  EPiSODE iNFO 
                                                        
                                                                        
  For hundreds of years, people have been documenting, recording and    
  obsessing about the weather, and 2012 has provided much to talk       
  about, from droughts and gale-force winds to summer floods. With the  
  use of archive footage, expert insight and computer graphics, this    
  programme investigates the UK's most severe weather events of the     
  past decade and puts them into the wider context of climate change.   
                                                                        
  Enjoy!
